                <h2 class="post-title"><a href="http://hyperthinker.wpengine.com/2014/sharing-ideas-with-peter-ryan-day-4/">Sharing ideas with Peter Ryan: Day 4</a></h2>
                        <div class="post-meta">
                        <div class="meta-left">
                <span class="postdate">Nov 20th 2014&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
                <span class="postauthor">By: Philip Weiss</span></span>
            </div>
                        <div class="meta-right">
                                <span class="postcomments"><a href="http://hyperthinker.wpengine.com/2014/sharing-ideas-with-peter-ryan-day-4/#respond">No comments</a></span>
                                            </div>
            <div class="clear"></div>
        </div>
                <div class="post-content">
                        <p>Today was a day packed with back to back lectures, and I switched between introducing Hyperthinking to explaining digital mapping, as I did with the students of the University of Alberta on Monday.  The students worked on different research methodologies so the discussions we had after the presentation were very interesting with students investigating the role of digital research in research projects. It is interesting to find that digital research is still quite rare and not something that is taught systematically although most teachers recognize the importance.</p>
<p><a href="http://hyperthinker.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Phil-whiteboard-1.jpg"><img class="alignleft size-large wp-image-870" title="Phil whiteboard-1" src="http://hyperthinker.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Phil-whiteboard-1-1024x778.jpg" alt="" width="614" height="467" srcset="http://hyperthinker.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Phil-whiteboard-1-1024x778.jpg 1024w, http://hyperthinker.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Phil-whiteboard-1-300x228.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 614px) 100vw, 614px" /></a></p>
<p>I had the opportunity to interview MacEwan University&#8217;s CIO and communications professor, Peter Ryan. Ryan attended a presentation on digital mapping followed by a lecture on Hyperthinking, and provided insights on bringing together different approaches with a common goal. It was very interesting to compare Peter´s academic point of view on methodologies with that of ZN Consulting on both, Hyperthinking and Digital Mapping.</p>
<p><iframe width="500" height="281" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/dtl_CEZRlTc?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe></p>
<p>I also launched the &#8216;Hyperthinking Club&#8217;, an initiative for students who want to continue or start Hyperthinking and share their experience of this with others.  It is a very straightforward idea: meet once a month, share ideas and experience on what works and what you picked up, and continue sharing the experience on Facebook. We will see where this takes us.</p>
<p><img class="alignleft size-large wp-image-860" title="Classroom" src="http://hyperthinker.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Classroom-1024x768.jpg" alt="" width="614" height="461" srcset="http://hyperthinker.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Classroom-1024x768.jpg 1024w, http://hyperthinker.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Classroom-300x225.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 614px) 100vw, 614px" /></p>
<p>Thursday is a day of key public presentations with a very practical session on Hyperthinking in the healthcare I will be introducing a case study on <a href="http://www.breakdengue.org">Break Dengue</a> an initiative I co-founded over a year ago. Check back tomorrow for the latest updates from Canada and don&#8217;t forget to follow us on Twitter where you can join the discussion using the hashtag #hyperthinking.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Some of the conversation going on on Twitter…</p>
<p><a href="http://hyperthinker.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Screen-Shot-2014-11-20-at-15.56.41.png"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-880" title="Screen Shot 2014-11-20 at 15.56.41" src="http://hyperthinker.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Screen-Shot-2014-11-20-at-15.56.41.png" alt="" width="581" height="102" srcset="http://hyperthinker.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Screen-Shot-2014-11-20-at-15.56.41.png 581w, http://hyperthinker.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Screen-Shot-2014-11-20-at-15.56.41-300x52.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 581px) 100vw, 581px" /></a></p>
<p><a href="http://hyperthinker.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Screen-Shot-2014-11-20-at-15.56.191.png"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-878" title="Screen Shot 2014-11-20 at 15.56.19" src="http://hyperthinker.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Screen-Shot-2014-11-20-at-15.56.191.png" alt="" width="578" height="91" srcset="http://hyperthinker.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Screen-Shot-2014-11-20-at-15.56.191.png 578w, http://hyperthinker.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Screen-Shot-2014-11-20-at-15.56.191-300x47.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 578px) 100vw, 578px" /></a><a href="http://hyperthinker.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Screen-Shot-2014-11-20-at-15.56.31.png"><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-879" title="Screen Shot 2014-11-20 at 15.56.31" src="http://hyperthinker.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Screen-Shot-2014-11-20-at-15.56.31.png" alt="" width="577" height="99" srcset="http://hyperthinker.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Screen-Shot-2014-11-20-at-15.56.31.png 577w, http://hyperthinker.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/Screen-Shot-2014-11-20-at-15.56.31-300x51.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 577px) 100vw, 577px" /></a></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
